RepresentativenessTest::representativenessCore
├── when a structural strike tick is derived for a human rate
│   └── it equals the decimal-gap-correct snapped tick exactly at the K_hi strike
├── when the regime-conditional width is derived
│   └── it differs from the stationary GBM baseline width when the regime is stress
├── when the regime-conditional vol is derived
│   └── it strictly exceeds the stationary baseline vol when the regime is stress
├── when beta one is applied across regimes
│   └── it makes the stress inflation adjustment strictly exceed the tranquil one
├── when the regime oracle is stale or unset
│   ├── given observedAt is zero
│   │   └── it resolves the effective regime to stress
│   └── given observedAt is beyond the max staleness window
│       └── it resolves the effective regime to stress
├── when a whole-usd notional is mapped to a feasible option ratio
│   └── it is a monotone non-decreasing map clamped between one and one hundred twenty seven
├── when the full geometry is resolved from a mandate-like input
│   └── it derives the expected hedge-leg fields field by field
└── when the geometry derivation is mutated to collapse stress beta one onto tranquil
    └── it makes the gbm divergence and asymmetry assertions vacuous
